## Role Snapshot
- Chief Product Officer responsible for shaping and prioritizing development work, ensuring timely high-quality delivery, and preserving product-market fit for Triage while incubating new product bets (e.g., Turbo Auth, reimbursement automation).
- Acts as coach and strategic partner to align product, engineering, and go-to-market execution with Exponential’s growth targets.
- Serves as connective tissue across product, delivery, customer experience, and data teams; escalates risks promptly and drives follow-through.

## Company Overview
- Exponential (exponentialcare.ai) empowers Post-Acute Care (PAC) teams—skilled nursing facilities (SNFs) and home health agencies (HHAs)—to review referrals, select the right patients, and fill beds faster through AI-assisted workflows.
- Current product line: `Triage` (live) with adjacent initiatives under exploration: `Turbo Auth` (prior authorization automation) and Medicare/Medicaid reimbursement automation.
- Strategic narrative: “Triage makes PACs more profitable—empower your team with cutting-edge AI. Review referrals, choose the right patients, and fill beds faster.”

